            <creation>This story, with the short title "Mary Heals a Traveller to a New Land," is recent: the earliest PEMM manuscript* in which this story appears is from around<date>1929</date>.Originally composed in <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName></creation>
            <abstract>
                <p>A man who loved Mary traveled to another land, where he became deathly ill. He went to a church dedicated to Mary and prayed for her to save him. He drank water from the church fount and recited the prayer Mary prayed at Golgotha, whereupon he made an immediate recovery.</p>
